                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12956803" author="alitokmen" created="Wed, 6 Oct 2010 13:01:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attaching patch&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12956909" author="hadrian" created="Wed, 6 Oct 2010 13:12:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for reporting this and for the patch. If provider is null, what happens?&lt;br/&gt;
Did you intend something like below?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; provider == &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt; ? &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt; : provider.getContinuation();
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12956910" author="alitokmen" created="Wed, 6 Oct 2010 13:18:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hello&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Yes, indeed I had meant your version &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The return being null is already checked by the caller, here is a snippet:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;                Continuation continuation = getContinuation(cxfExchange);
                if (continuation != null &amp;amp;&amp;amp; !endpoint.isSynchronous()) {
                    return asyncInvoke(cxfExchange, continuation);
                } else {
                    return syncInvoke(cxfExchange);
                }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12956808" author="hadrian" created="Wed, 6 Oct 2010 13:39:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks Savas, I&apos;ll apply the patch, you still get the credit &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12956950" author="davsclaus" created="Wed, 6 Oct 2010 15:08:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hadrian get in touch with willem as he knows this CXF continuation stuff and have worked on this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12956906" author="njiang" created="Thu, 7 Oct 2010 05:27:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;@Hadrian&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m OK with the patch, please apply it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12956905" author="njiang" created="Thu, 7 Oct 2010 05:29:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If you are using cxf-rt-http-jetty-transport or cxf-rt-jms-transport, there is always a ContinuationProvider, but if you are using other transport, you will get the NPE.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12956904" author="hadrian" created="Thu, 7 Oct 2010 06:07:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch applied with thanks to Savas (rev: 1005334). Keep them coming.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12956917" author="alitokmen" created="Thu, 7 Oct 2010 07:18:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Excellent &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Indeed, I&apos;m using the HTTP transport without Jetty, hence the NPE as Willem explained&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Cheers&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13023697" author="davsclaus" created="Sun, 24 Apr 2011 09:57:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Closing all resolved tickets from 2010 or older&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
